This paper is primarily focused on representation learning for natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of variational methods for learning Factorial Hidden Markov Models, which is a machine learning technique that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of global context in representation learning, which could potentially fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) or data structures and algorithms (cs.SD).
